        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens effective tool inventory metadata projection: active registry `toolMetadata` rows now use bounded reads so malformed metadata cannot crash runtime inventory construction before healthy plugin tools are listed\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `4126689b16f6ea5f117d4aadb5e6c88db80c8b5a`, proven after rebasing onto `origin/main` at `aa0d6e1bca55a662450ee69beefc0523d296349f`; GitHub `main` advanced afterward to `afa6d0cd1839e9f0040f52cb1ed9d25e37916ae3` and was not rechased\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/tools-effective-inventory-build.ts src/agents/tools-effective-inventory.test.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/validation.ts packages/agent-core/src/tool-name.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/agent-harness.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD -- src/agents/tools-effective-inventory-build.ts src/agents/tools-effective-inventory.test.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/validation.ts packages/agent-core/src/tool-name.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/agent-harness.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/tools-effective-inventory-build.ts src/agents/tools-effective-inventory.test.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/validation.ts packages/agent-core/src/tool-name.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.ts packages/agent-core/src/harness/agent-harness.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/tools-effective-inventory.test.ts packages/llm-core/src/validation.test.ts packages/agent-core/src/agent-loop.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 3 files passed, 26 tests passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean on the effective tool inventory metadata projection slice before the final rebase; the final rebase conflict was resolved by keeping `agent-core` as the `llm-core` validation re-export and moving the guarded tool lookup into `llm-core`\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, shared provider resolver projection, active runtime CLI backend projection, provider discovery entry projection, explicit web provider public artifact projection, document/web-content extractor public artifact projection, trusted tool policy decision handling, Gateway Control UI descriptor projection, Gateway plugin session action dispatch, dynamic plugin session action method-scope resolution, plugin-registered Gateway method descriptor scope resolution, channel plugin Gateway method discovery, `tools.catalog` active registry metadata projection, plugin inspect/status Gateway method summaries, plugin inspect/status registry-entry summaries, plugin inspect/status plugin-record projection, and effective tool inventory metadata projection no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, unreadable backend configs, unreadable CLI commands, hostile callback metadata, throwing provider/extractor factories, unreadable public artifact metadata, throwing trusted policy evaluators, unreadable trusted policy decision fields, unreadable gateway descriptor metadata, unreadable session action metadata, malformed matched action scopes, unreadable gateway method descriptor names/scopes, unreadable channel gateway method arrays/elements, unreadable tool metadata entries, unreadable tool metadata records, unreadable deferred tool entries, unreadable deferred tool ownership fields, unreadable inspect Gateway method descriptor owners/names, unreadable inspect typed hook/custom hook/tool/diagnostic/memory-provider registry fields, unreadable inspect plugin-record ids/kinds/summary arrays/metadata, or unreadable effective-inventory tool metadata rows while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, rebased onto `origin/main` at `aa0d6e1bca55a662450ee69beefc0523d296349f`; after push, GitHub `main` advanced to `afa6d0cd1839e9f0040f52cb1ed9d25e37916ae3` and this last base-only drift was not rechased.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: after the effective tool inventory metadata slice, ran focused formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, synthetic/private-name scrub, and autoreview commands listed in Verification; after rebasing onto the latest `origin/main`, resolved the moved `agent-core`/`llm-core` validation conflict and reran formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, and scrub on the rebased head.\n\nEvidence after fix: `tools-effective-inventory.test.ts` now covers unreadable `fuzzplugin` metadata rows, unreadable metadata entry getters, unreadable metadata tool-name getters, and a healthy `mockplugin` tool that still receives owned display name, description, risk, and tags; the conflict proof also covers unreadable sibling tool names in `llm-core` validation and `agent-core` execution.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed active registry tool metadata no longer aborts effective inventory construction; unreadable metadata rows are skipped, healthy plugin tool metadata remains scoped by plugin id plus tool name, existing unsupported-schema quarantine behavior still passes, and the moved validation seam still skips unreadable sibling tool names.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted effective tool inventory and validation conflict surfaces plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks. The final GitHub `main` drift from `aa0d6e1bca55a662450ee69beefc0523d296349f` to `afa6d0cd1839e9f0040f52cb1ed9d25e37916ae3` was not rechased after the clean rebase/proof/push loop.\n",
